AmaXhosa King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu's funeral has begun. He died on November 14, 2019 at age 51. JOHANNESBURG - AmaXhosa King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu has been laid to rest in Willowvale, Eastern Cape. He was honoured with an official funeral by the president. 29 November 2019 - Guests mourn AmaXhosa King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu. President Cyril Ramaphosa attends AmaXhosa King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu. President Cyril Ramaphosa pays his respects to AmaXhosa King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu. Former president, Thabo Mbeki attends the funeral of AmaXhosa King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu.